# Builder / Live Parity

What the builder shows must match draft preview and published live. See `AGENTS.md` §6.

## Render

- Use `lib/liveRenderer.js` for all three surfaces.
- Do not duplicate widget markup in builder-only components.

## CSS layout

Target the parity surface only:

```css
:is(.live-doc, .bld-canvas__live-mirror) …
```

Import `PARITY_SURFACE_SELECTOR` from `lib/paritySurface.js` when generating selectors in JS.

**Do not** set `overflow`, `height`, `max-height`, or `object-fit` on live widgets via:

- `.bld-canvas__page …`
- `.bld-demo-* …` (except `pointer-events` / editing chrome)

Put widget layout in `styles/shared/*`:

- `feature-tabs.css` — feature tabs
- `section-template-parity.css` — FAQ, blogs, hero, carousel, other `data-section-template` rows

Do not re-add bare `.live-doc [data-section-template='…']` layout rules in `live-site.css` or `builder-live-mirror.css`.

## Inline contracts

If global `.live-doc img` or device CSS can override sizing:

1. Add `lib/<widget>Image.js` (or similar) with inline styles.
2. Register in `PARITY_INLINE_STYLE_CONTRACTS` (`lib/paritySurface.js`).
3. Mark DOM with a `data-*` attribute.

## Before merge

```bash
npm test
npm run audit:builder-live-parity
```

New widgets must pass `tests/builderLiveParityAudit.test.mjs`.
